-- Barclays agrees $3.1 million pay-off with Diamond: Sky
-- 
-- Tue Jul 10, 2012 4:56am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/07/10/us-barclays-diamond-idUSBRE8690DO20120710

 

 LONDON  (Reuters) - Barclays has agreed a pay-off worth about 2 million pounds ($3.1 million) for Bob Diamond, its former chief executive who quit last week following an interest rate rigging scandal, Sky News reported. 
 Diamond quit on July 3. He took home about 17 million pounds last year, including previous bonus awards that vested, and was entitled to a year's salary worth 1.4 million pounds. ($1 = 0.6442 British pounds) (Reporting by  Steve Slater )